Class Set

java.lang.Object
  se.lypson.common.collections.Set
All Implemented Interfaces:
ISet
Direct Known Subclasses:
CountingSet
public class Set
extends java.lang.Object
implements ISet

A class for storing elements without duplicates or a specified order (as in the mathematical set concept).

Thread Safety:
Static methods are thread-safe. Instance methods are not guaranteed to be thread-safe.

Author:
Tobias Persson

addAll

public void addAll(java.util.Enumeration enumeration)

Adds all elements in an enumeration to the set.

The general contract for addAll is that it must call add for each element in the enumeration (unless an exception is thrown).

Parameters:
enumeration - an enumeration of the element to add to the set.
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if the enumeration or an element in the enumeration is null. Elements in the enumeration added before the null value was encountered are still added, the remaining elements in the enumeration are not.
